    <h2>1. Executive Summary</h2>
    <p>
      AppLovin Corporation operates a leading marketing software platform providing mobile app developers with comprehensive tools for growth, user acquisition, monetization, and measurement—powered by its proprietary machine learning engine (AXON).
      The company primarily serves the mobile gaming industry while expanding into additional verticals. Following a strategic pivot away from first-party game development to focus on its higher-margin
      software platform business, AppLovin has demonstrated strong execution with revenue growth and significant margin expansion. Key investment considerations include its technological advantage, market positioning, competitive dynamics, and evolving platform policies.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Company Overview</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      Understanding AppLovin's business model, technology, and market position.
    </p>

    <div class="data-grid">
      <div class="data-grid-item">
        <h4>Business Model</h4>
        <p>
          AppLovin provides an integrated technology stack enabling mobile app developers to market, monetize, analyze, and publish their applications—focusing primarily on mobile gaming. The company operates two key segments:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Software Platform:</strong> High-margin business including AppDiscovery, MAX mediation, and Adjust for attribution.</li>
          <li><strong>Apps (Legacy):</strong> Previously featured owned/operated mobile games; now minimized in favor of higher-margin offerings.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="data-grid-item">
        <h4>Technology & Differentiation</h4>
        <p>
          The AXON machine learning engine forms the backbone of AppLovin's competitive advantage, enabling:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Advanced audience targeting and ad optimization</li>
          <li>Automated media spend allocation for maximum ROI</li>
          <li>Real-time performance measurement</li>
          <li>Continuous algorithmic improvements</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="data-grid-item">
        <h4>Market Position</h4>
        <p>
          AppLovin operates within the rapidly evolving mobile advertising and app monetization ecosystem:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Strong position in the mobile gaming vertical</li>
          <li>Expanding into non-gaming applications</li>
          <li>Impacted by platform ecosystem changes (e.g., Apple ATT, Google Privacy Sandbox)</li>
          <li>Global footprint with exposure to major mobile markets</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

