    <h2>6. Competitor Analysis</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      Examination of the competitive landscape and AppLovin's position relative to industry peers.
    </p>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Competitor</th>
          <th>Primary Overlap</th>
          <th>Relative Strengths</th>
          <th>Relative Weaknesses</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Unity Software (U)</strong></td>
          <td>Ad monetization, user acquisition, analytics</td>
          <td>
            Broader game development ecosystem, engine ownership
          </td>
          <td>
            Less focused on pure ad optimization; integration challenges with ironSource
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Meta Platforms (META)</strong></td>
          <td>Mobile app advertising, Audience Network</td>
          <td>
            Enormous scale, data advantage from social graph
          </td>
          <td>
            Less specialized in gaming; diversified business lines
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Google (GOOGL)</strong></td>
          <td>Google Ads, AdMob, app distribution</td>
          <td>
            Android ecosystem, search dominance, robust data capabilities
          </td>
          <td>
            Less focused on gaming-specific ad tech; regulatory scrutiny
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Digital Turbine (APPS)</strong></td>
          <td>App distribution, advertising technology</td>
          <td>
            Strong OEM/carrier integrations
          </td>
          <td>
            Smaller scale, less advanced AI
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>The Trade Desk (TTD)</strong></td>
          <td>Programmatic advertising technology</td>
          <td>
            Wide digital channel focus
          </td>
          <td>
            Different customer base; less app-specific expertise
          </td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>Competitive Advantages:</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Integrated Platform:</strong> A comprehensive solution combining UA, monetization, and analytics.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>AXON AI Technology:</strong> Advanced machine learning capabilities for superior campaign optimization.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Mobile Gaming Expertise:</strong> A leading position in the largest mobile app vertical.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Scale and Data:</strong> Significant data volume drives optimization and network effects.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Neutral Mediation:</strong> The MAX platform is seen as independent compared to in-house solutions.
      </li>
    </ul>

